Based on the provided evidence, we see several key points supporting the concept of ionization being critical in radiation-induced cell death. Hydroxyl radical formation from ionized water molecules interacts with DNA, leading to strand breaks and potentially carcinogenesis. Additionally, the intrinsic and extrinsic pathways of apoptosis are triggered by DNA damage mediated through ionizing radiation. While there are mentions of mitochondrial involvement and charring of nucleoproteins, the overarching theme remains focused on the fundamental role of ionization in initiating cellular damage. Thus, despite nuanced explanations involving secondary mechanisms, the core mechanism still revolves around ionization. My revised stance agrees with option C: Ionization. \boxed{C}
